(99, 0, 'news', 'no-alias', 'Ukrainian independent label CTS presents 4 new releases!', NULL, 'Vinyl singl called &ldquo;Be yourself&rdquo; by Sergio Mega is an international creative project. The base of song text is a legend about medieval manuscript which was found in the church of Sainted Paul, in Baltimore. The manuscript is dated 1692. The text that was adapted by Max Erman was performed by vocalist from Australia &ndash; Storm Tarrion. There&rsquo;re four remixes on the vinyl. There is an Original version, also remix by DJ Derbastler, remix by DJ Small, and special Phobia mix from Italian DJ and producer M.I.D.I. Pre-release was presented on Miami Winter Conference in March 2007. The date of the official release &ndash; is on April, the 12th, 2007. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img height=\"200\" width=\"200\" src=\"/images/tobуcontinued500.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is mixed compilation called &bdquo;To be continued&hellip;&rdquo; by CTS Records &ndash; the first part on the CD. There&rsquo;re 12 tracks in this album by the European including Ukrainian and Russian producers. Next to the star names of world dancefloor like Dahool, Trik &amp; Kubic, Coburn are the names of the well-known and the new Ukrainian and Russian producers &ndash; DJ Derbastler,Sergio Mega, DJ Small, Dan Brain, Sambooca.<br />\r\nThe final track is the remix by DJ Tiesel аkа Sergey Tovstoluzhskiy. In this compilation <br />\r\nare presented works of labels like CTS, Ministry of Sound, Great Stuff, Recordings, Sumo, Kompakt and others. Album style is &ndash; Electro, House, Techno. The mix was madden by Sergio Mega who&rsquo;d been known earlier as DJ Megabeat<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img height=\"200\" width=\"200\" src=\"/images/Trust_me300(3).jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nVinyl singles &laquo;Trust me&raquo; and &laquo;Synthetic People&raquo; by Sergio Mega were performed in Amsterdam as a part of the international festival Amsterdam Dance Event in October, 2006. The vinyls have got many excellent reviews from the professionals of the whole world. Among DJs who have included tracks &laquo;Trust me&raquo; and &laquo;Synthetic People&raquo; in their playlists are &ndash;- DJ Tarkan, who is well known by Ukrainian audience, Deep Dish remixer - Sultan, The Mystic Force, Coldrush, Ariel Cybana, Onirika, DJ Mute and many others. More than 30 radio stations of the whole world have included these tracks in the rotation. Especially for Ukrainian fans CTS label has published theirs limited edition on CDs. The releases aren&rsquo;t the simple copies of the vinyl originals but they complemented by the two new Electro bonus tracks from CTS label artists - &laquo;Soon&raquo; (it shell begin&hellip;) by DJ Small and &laquo;I ball II&raquo; by Dan Brain.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img height=\"200\" width=\"200\" src=\"/images/Synthetic_people_single500\'(1).jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />\r\n<br />', NULL, 'Ukrainian independent label CTS presents 4 new releases!', NULL, './../images/99_s.jpg', NULL, NULL, '2009-04-08 13:00:25', '2009-04-01', 'yes', 'no', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(100, 0, 'news', 'no-alias', 'Mixed compilation “To be continued…” ', NULL, 'This is mixed compilation called &bdquo;To be continued&hellip;&rdquo; by CTS Records &ndash; the first part on the CD. There&rsquo;re 12 tracks in this album by the European including Ukrainian and Russian producers. Next to the star names of world dancefloor like Dahool, Trik &amp; Kubic, Coburn are the names of the well-known and the new Ukrainian and Russian producers &ndash; DJ Derbastler,Sergio Mega, DJ Small, Dan Brain, Sambooca.<br />\r\nThe final track is the remix by DJ Tiesel аkа Sergey Tovstoluzhskiy. In this compilation <br />\r\nare presented works of labels like CTS, Ministry of Sound, Great Stuff, Recordings, Sumo, Kompakt and others. Album style is &ndash; Electro, House, Techno. The mix was madden by Sergio Mega who&rsquo;d been known earlier as DJ Megabeat.<br />\r\n<br />', NULL, 'Mixed compilation “To be continued…”', NULL, './../images/100_s.jpg', NULL, NULL, '2009-04-08 13:00:25', '2009-04-01', 'yes', 'no', 2, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(101, 0, 'news', 'no-alias', '“I’m your extazy” from Sergio Mega', NULL, 'We present for you the newest release by &ldquo;CTS Records&rdquo;- &ldquo;I&rsquo;m your extazy&rdquo; from Sergio Mega. This release includes an original version and three remixes including remix by Zavoloka in Minimal style. Zavoloka is well-known and active performer in the area of experimental music. She is known by participating in different, world festivals: &ldquo;Being the future&rdquo; (Berlin), &ldquo;Unsound&rdquo; (Kharkov), &ldquo;Les Urbaines&rdquo; (Switzerland), &quot;Cimatics&quot; (Belgium), Minimax&quot;(Slovakia), &quot;Garage&quot; (Germany),&quot;La nuit bleue&rdquo; (France), &quot;Kontra-musik&quot; (Sweden), &quot;Radius&quot; (Austria), &quot;Ambush!&quot;(Poland), &quot;Femmes&quot;(Belgium), &quot;Clubtransmediale&quot; (Germany), &quot;Fragments of the Sound&quot; (Ukraine).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis release has got the high estimation of sound quality and actuality of the presented musical product from DJs and producers of the whole world:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;No pills needed here. This track will get you feeling that feeling!! Excellent!&rdquo;<br />\r\nJustin George - Family Productions/Sound Therapy/NM Sessions (United States)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&laquo;love the tweak and build on it. sounds super fun and I\'m going to give it a try for sure. thanks!&raquo;<br />\r\nJ e l o - BugeyedRecords/2Wars/Eden Recordings/Universal (Canada)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Ikiro remix)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Very Good!&rdquo;<br />\r\nSultan &ndash; Yoshitoshi/Release Records/Tao/Swift (Canada)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&rdquo;Very good! Dynamical!&rdquo;<br />\r\nRoma Pafos &ndash; Mediadrive records(Latvia)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Ikiro remix)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;lovely&rdquo;<br />\r\nJames Sanderlin &ndash; BPP / Van Nuys (USA)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Electric Ambiente mix)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;I have to give this a full listen.  I love the melody. Very unique...beautiful.  I don\\\'t care for any of the other versions, but it sounds like this has great potential.&rdquo;<br />\r\nSpector Selector - Top Radio FM (Belgium)/O\'Key Radio FM (Russia)/Native Radio FM (Russia)/Puls Radio FM (Russia)/Fresh FM 92.7 (Australia)/Planeta FM (Poland)/WRHU FM (New York City)/TopFM (Serbia)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Electric Ambient mix)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;nice vocals and sireny sounds, good bass&rdquo;<br />\r\nBoris Gluck &ndash; Club Five/Progressive Felonies (Washington D.C. / USA)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;this is cool, i could go for a dub mix, but this one might grown on me.&rdquo;<br />\r\nDirty &ndash; LFO Radio/Electric Soul Patrol/WEVL (Memphis / USA)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Sergio got it going on!&rdquo;<br />\r\nMarcus Wortley &ndash; abletonlivedj.com/progressivehouse.com/progcast/Future/DMC/EDJ (USA)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Catchy bass, I like how it builds up with the vocal, sound quality is a bit off (maybe will sound different on the big speakers) but it sounded a little distorted or like it was underwater.&rdquo;<br />\r\nElroy &ndash; BeatPimpz, Ryan Dykstra Nightlife, Twenty40 (USA)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;nice voice and good for a killer night&rdquo;<br />\r\nDJ Pepe Camil &ndash; The Underexposed/Nordika/Supernova (Mexico)<br />\r\nabout Sergio Mega &ndash; I&rsquo;m your extasy (Original)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />', NULL, '“I’m your extazy” from Sergio Mega', NULL, './../images/101_s.jpg', NULL, NULL, '2009-04-08 13:00:25', '2009-04-01', 'yes', 'no', 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
